    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera represents the pinnacle of the 996.2 generation, preserved in concours-level condition. The 3.6L flat-six engine features VarioCam Plus valve timing and has been fastidiously maintained with a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement. Power is routed through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a short-throw shifter, providing tactile and precise engagement. The chassis is enhanced by a Bilstein PSS10 coilover system and GT3-spec adjustable sway bars, offering exceptional lateral grip and turn-in response. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, shrouded by lightweight BBS forged wheels wrapped in fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber. With zero fluid seepage and a pristine undercarriage, this specimen is a turn-key investment for the serious driver.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Vehicle is in mint condition. Flawless original paint. Interior is like new. No mechanical issues. Full service records available.",
      "price": 43500.0,
